sql:
SELECT freelancers.*, skillsets.skill, skillsets.proficiency_level 
FROM freelancers 
JOIN skillsets ON freelancers.freelancer_id = skillsets.freelancer_id;

SELECT first_name, middle_name, last_name, email, phone, address, city, state, postal_code, standard_rate, weekend_rate, date_of_birth, gender, biography
FROM freelancers
WHERE freelancer_id = '1';

SELECT DISTINCT f.first_name, f.middle_name, f.last_name
FROM freelancers f
JOIN documents d ON f.freelancer_id = d.freelancer_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM freelancers 
WHERE CAST(standard_rate AS REAL) > 50.00;

external_knowledge:
- In metaphorical terms, freelancers are referred to as "wayfarers", projects as "voyages", and hours worked are translated into "sabbaticals" to reflect time spent.;
- The concept of a week having 4 working days is used to translate hours into weeks, resembling sabbatical periods.;
- The proportion of the total project time reflects how much of the voyage timeframe a wayfarer has explored in metaphorical terms.

- "sailing the seas" metaphorically refers to companies operating or making progress;
- "welcoming the dawn of a new era since the start of 2022" means projects started after January 1, 2022;
- "ships manned by sailors who possess the winds of React expertise" refers to projects involving freelancers with intermediate proficiency in React;
- "storm of unpaid dues" metaphorically refers to pending payments for project assignments;
- "reached out to these enterprises through the waves of communication" indicates messages sent by freelancers to clients.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT pa.freelancer_id) 
FROM reviews r
JOIN project_assignments pa ON r.assignment_id = pa.assignment_id;

external_knowledge:
- "long-term projects" refers to projects lasting more than 180 days;
- "significant earnings" means the freelancer has earned more than $5000 on the project based on their hourly rate and hours worked;
- The list is ranked from the freelancer with the most qualifying projects to the least.
